<section id="introduction" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p>This is the first article published on my technical blog.</p>
<p>The purpose of this post is to verify that Quarto correctly renders:</p>
<ul>
<li>mathematical equations;</li>
<li>Python code;</li>
<li>Jupyter output;</li>
<li>figures;</li>
<li>links to external repositories.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="a-mathematical-example" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="a-mathematical-example">A mathematical example</h2>
<p>Consider the mean squared error:</p>
<p><span id="eq-mse"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cmathcal%7BL%7D(%5Ctheta)%0A=%0A%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BN%7D%0A%5Csum_%7Bi=1%7D%5E%7BN%7D%0A%5Cleft(f_%5Ctheta(x_i)-y_i%5Cright)%5E2%0A%5Ctag%7B1%7D"></span></p>
<p>Equation Equation&nbsp;1 measures the average squared difference between predictions and targets.</p>
</section>
